[size=12pt][b][color=#FF00FF]📐 Mathematical Proof: Performance Independence[/color][/b][/size]

We've published a [b]complete mathematical proof[/b] in our academic whitepaper demonstrating that time-based halving achieves performance independence.

[b]Download Full Whitepaper with Mathematical Proofs:[/b]
[url=https://drive.proton.me/urls/4VJ9CYH98W#Ibg1AdOuYewX]Quantum Physics Whitepaper - Time-Based Halving (39 pages)[/url]

[b]Theorem:[/b] For any constant blocks-per-second rate [i]b > 0[/i], time-based halving converges to target annual emission [i]E_target[/i] regardless of [i]b[/i].

[code]Let r(t) = R₀ >> ⌊(t - t_genesis) / T_year⌋

Annual emission:
E(year_n) = ∫₀^T_year b × r(t) dt
          = b × T_year × (R₀ / 2^n)

Setting E(year_1) = E_target:
E_target = b × T_year × R₀

Therefore R₀ = E_target / (b × T_year)

Thus E(year) → E_target regardless of b, QED.[/code]

[b][color=#00FF94]First cryptocurrency with mathematically proven performance-agnostic tokenomics![/color][/b]

