[size=12pt][b][color=#FF00FF]Security Considerations[/color][/b][/size]

[b]Attack Vector:[/b] Miners could manipulate timestamps to affect rewards.

[b]Mitigation:[/b]
[list]
[li]✅ [b]Consensus-level timestamp validation[/b] (±2 hours tolerance)[/li]
[li]✅ [b]Median-time-past (MTP)[/b] from recent blocks[/li]
[li]✅ [b]Network time protocol (NTP)[/b] synchronization[/li]
[li]✅ [b]Byzantine fault tolerance[/b] in validator set[/li]
[/list]

[b]Risk Assessment:[/b] Low. Timestamp manipulation provides minimal benefit compared to honest mining.

